# Step 14: Reports for AI-Powered Customer Support Ticketing System

Reports help support managers monitor case workload, priority distribution, and agent performance.
In this step, we create two important reports using the **Cases object**.

---

# Report 1: Open Cases by Priority

## Purpose

This report shows all **open cases grouped by priority** so managers can quickly identify urgent issues.

---

# Step-by-Step Implementation

## Step 1: Open Report Builder

1. Open **App Launcher**
2. Search for **Reports**
3. Click **Reports**
4. Click **New Report**

---

# Step 2: Select Report Type

1. Choose **Cases**
2. Click **Continue**

---

# Step 3: Apply Filters

Click **Filters** and configure the following:

Show Me
All Cases

Created Date
All Time

Enable
✔ Update Preview Automatically

Add Filter:

Field
Status

Operator
Not Equal To

Value
Closed

This ensures only **open cases** appear in the report.

---

# Step 4: Add Columns

Add the following fields:

* Case Number
* Subject
* Priority
* Status
* Case Owner

These columns provide details about each open case.

---

# Step 5: Group by Priority

Drag **Priority** into the **Group Rows** section.

This will group cases into categories such as:

* High
* Medium
* Low

---

# Step 6: Save and Run Report

Click **Save & Run**

Report Name
Open Cases by Priority

Report Folder
Public Reports

---

# Result

The report displays all **open cases grouped by priority**, helping support managers quickly identify high-priority issues.

---

# Report 2: Agent Performance Report

## Purpose

This report tracks **agent workload and efficiency** by analyzing how quickly cases are resolved.

---

# Step-by-Step Implementation

## Step 1: Create New Report

1. Go to **Reports**
2. Click **New Report**
3. Select **Cases**
4. Click **Continue**

---

# Step 2: Apply Filters

Configure the following filters:

Show Me
All Cases

Created Date
All Time

Status
Closed

This ensures the report only shows **completed cases**.

---

# Step 3: Add Columns

Add these fields:

* Case Number
* Owner
* Priority
* Created Date
* Closed Date
* Resolution Time (Hours)

These fields help evaluate agent performance.

---

# Step 4: Group by Agent

Drag **Owner** into **Group Rows**.

This groups cases by the **support agent** responsible for them.

---

# Step 5: Add Summary Calculation

1. Click the **Resolution Time (Hours)** field
2. Select **Summarize**
3. Choose **Average**

This calculates the **average resolution time per agent**.

---

# Step 6: Save and Run Report

Report Name
Agent Performance Report

Report Folder
Public Reports

Click **Save & Run**

---

# Result

This report helps managers:

* Measure agent productivity
* Track resolution speed
* Identify workload distribution

It improves overall **support team performance monitoring** in the AI-powered ticketing system.
